# Frontend build env
# ───────────────────
# The Google Calendar integration no longer needs a build-time client ID. The OAuth client ID +
# secret now live server-side in the Cloudflare Pages Functions (see functions/api/auth/google),
# and the browser holds only a runtime "app secret" entered in Settings. So there are currently no
# VITE_* variables required to build the frontend.
#
# Server-side OAuth config is NOT set here — it's configured on the Cloudflare Pages project as
# secrets/vars (and a KV namespace binding). See docs/deployment.md. Required there:
#   GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID       — Google OAuth "Web application" client ID
#   GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET   — Google OAuth client secret (server-only)
#   APP_SHARED_SECRET      — the single shared secret guarding the Worker endpoints
#   APP_ORIGIN (optional)  — overrides the auto-detected public origin
#   OAUTH_KV (binding)     — KV namespace holding the refresh token + cached access token
#
# For local dev with the Functions, run `npx wrangler pages dev` and put the same values in a
# gitignored `.dev.vars` file at the repo root.
